Appendix B — Example API request samples (curl)
1) Login
curl -X POST "http://localhost:8000/api/v1/auth/login" -H "Content-Type: application/json" -d '{"email":"admin@example.com","password":"Password123"}'

2) Start assessment (protected)
curl -X POST "http://localhost:8000/api/v1/assessment/start" -H "Authorization: Bearer <TOKEN>" -H "Content-Type: application/json" -d '{"title":"Quarterly Survey"}'

3) Employee start (invite token)
curl -X POST "http://localhost:8000/api/v1/employee-assessment/start" -H "x-invite-token: <INVITE_TOKEN>"

Appendix C — Postman collection
- Recommended: export a Postman collection with environment variables: baseUrl, adminToken, inviteToken. Include tests for login, invite, start, submit, and export.

